# New Architecture Rules

You are an expert Next.js developer working in a workspace that enforces a strict Bounded Context + Vertical Slice architecture. Follow every rule below on every file you create or modify.

## Folder Structure

```
src/
  app/        ← Next.js App Router ONLY
  contexts/   ← Business domain (Bounded Contexts + Vertical Slices)
  shared/     ← Shared Kernel — NO business logic
```

Dependency flow: app/ → contexts/{name}/index.ts → shared/. NEVER reverse.

## Import Rules (build errors if violated)

- contexts/A MUST NOT import from contexts/B/features/... — use contexts/B/index.ts
- app/ MUST NOT import from contexts/{name}/features/... — use contexts/{name}/index.ts
- shared/ MUST NOT import from contexts/
- contexts/ MUST NOT import from app/
- service.ts and use-cases.ts MUST NOT import from react, next/*, or shared/next
- Always use @/ path aliases for cross-feature imports

## Feature Structure

Minimum (CRUD): model.ts + api.ts + components/ + index.ts
Add only when justified:
- dto.ts + mapper.ts → backend contract differs from domain shape
- service.ts → business logic beyond simple CRUD
- use-cases.ts → api.ts orchestration grows complex
- store.ts → cross-component global UI state needed
- ports.ts → infrastructure is unstable or swappable

## model.ts
- Zod schemas ONLY. Types inferred via z.infer<>.
- Zero business logic. Zero framework imports.

## service.ts
- Pure TypeScript. ZERO imports from react, next, next/*, shared/next, browser APIs.
- Pure functions only. Throws DomainError from @/shared/errors.
- Testable with plain Jest — no providers, no framework mocks.

## api.ts (Server Actions)
- Always starts with 'use server'
- Validates ALL inputs with Zod safeParse
- Checks session/auth BEFORE business logic
- Returns ActionResult<T> from @/shared/types/action-result
- Delegates to service.ts or use-cases.ts — never implements business logic inline
- Catches DomainError → returns { ok: false, error: err.code }
- Never exposes stack traces

## components/ Convention
- {Feature}Page.tsx = RSC (no 'use client'): fetch data, validate session, pass to Shell
- {Feature}Shell.tsx = 'use client': interactive state, events, charts, grids, hooks
- Presentation components = pure (props in, callbacks out, no fetch, no global state)

## hooks/
- Encapsulate UI behavior: filtering, sorting, local interaction state
- DO NOT execute business logic
- DO NOT call fetch directly — use React Query

## dto.ts + mapper.ts
- dto.ts mirrors exact backend API shape (snake_case, legacy naming)
- mapper.ts converts DTO ↔ domain type
- DTOs NEVER leak beyond mapper.ts

## State Management
- Server state → React Query (useQuery/useMutation) in hooks/
- Global UI state → Jotai atoms in store.ts
- Local state → useState/useReducer inside the component
- React Query keys MUST be prefixed by context: ['cart', id], not just [id]
- NEVER mirror server data in Jotai atoms (two sources of truth = bugs)
- NEVER use React Query for pure UI state like isDrawerOpen

## Error Hierarchy (from @/shared/errors)
- DomainError → business rule violated (throw in service.ts)
- ValidationError → invalid input
- UnauthorizedError → missing/invalid session
Flow: service.ts throws → api.ts catches → ActionResult<T> → useMutation → UI message

## Shared Kernel (shared/)
Directories: api/ errors/ hooks/ types/ utils/ lib/ ui/ next/
Promotion criteria: used by 3+ features across DIFFERENT contexts AND no domain semantics.
- shared/ui/ = generic primitives only (Button, Modal, Badge, Input, Spinner)
- Domain-named components (CartBadge, OrderStatusChip) belong in their context
- service.ts and use-cases.ts NEVER import from shared/next/

## index.ts (MANDATORY)
- Every feature folder MUST have index.ts exporting its public API
- Every context folder MUST have index.ts exporting its public API

## app/ Layer
Allowed: route segments, metadata, error/loading boundaries, revalidatePath/revalidateTag, multi-context composition
FORBIDDEN: business rules, logic from service.ts, imports from contexts/{name}/features/...

## Common Anti-patterns to Refuse
- Business logic in hooks → extract to service.ts
- Importing contexts/B/features/... from context A → use contexts/B/index.ts
- CartBadge in shared/ui/ → move to contexts/cart/
- Server data in Jotai atom → use React Query
- Orchestration in api.ts → extract to use-cases.ts
- next/headers in service.ts → move to api.ts

See templates/ for feature and context scaffolds.
See architecture.md for full rationale and examples.
